description:
Hawkeye's back in a bad way. Armed and dangerous, Clint Barton is tasked with his most perilous mission yet. And what he discovers will reverberate across the entire Ultimate Universe when he finds himself in the middle of an international arms race.

But on the brink of obtaining a serum that will change the course of mutant history, has the eagle-eyed hero aimed too high to succeed?

Collecting Ultimate Comics Hawkeye #1-4.
name: Ultimate Comics Hawkeye by Hickman

description: When the swingin' seventies arrived, Marvel was there to welcome it with a host of new characters and titles! Assembled in one volume for the very first time are the fabulous first issues of dozens of Marvel's finest offerings from the seventies, including the likes of Dracula, Man-Thing, Luke Cage, and Tigra, not to mention such solo breakouts as the Black Widow and the Beast. Westerns, war, sci-fi, super heroes, monsters and mutants! Collecting AMAZING ADVENTURES (1970) #1, #11 and #18; SAVAGE TALES (1971) #1; MARVEL SPOTLIGHT (1971) #1-2 AND #5; MARVEL FEATURE (1971) #1; MARVEL PREMIERE #1: TOMB OF DRACULA #1; HERO FOR HIRE #1; COMBAT KELLY & THE DEADLY DOZEN #1; OUTLAW KID (1970) #10; GUNHAWKS #1; THE CAT #1: SHANNA THE SHE-DEVIL (1972) #1; and MONSTER OF FRANKENSTEIN #1.
name: Volume One

description: Join Wendel Trupstock and his significant other, Ollie Chalmers, as they navigate gay life in the '80s. Howard Cruse's Wendel ran in The Advocate during one of the most tumultuous periods in gay history, and the lives of his characters are a snapshot of the era-from the bar scene to long term commitments, from AIDS to activism, from Reagan to right-wing homophobia. Big issues and everyday life mingle in this strip with hilarious results. And Cruse is a master with pen and ink! Wendel All Together brings readers this classic comic strip complete in one volume for the first time ever!
name: Wendel All Together

In the metropolis of Lower Triton, the citys greatest hero, Virtue, its nastiest villain, Malice, and a run-of-the-mill guy named Jeff have something very important in common. Theyre all the same guy and none of them knows ituntil now! When Jeff stumbles upon Malices diabolical plan to murder Virtue, he has to step in way over his head, to try to save himself all three of himself from himself!

Jeff finds himself spiraling deeper and deeper into his fractured personalities, bouncing from crisis to crisis a wife he doesnt know; a cabal of super-villains; and a rampaging sub-humanoid threat to the city! In the end Jeffs toughest battle is the one he is least expecting the battle within himself!

In this climactic finale, our hero finds himself struggling to maintain his sanity as he battles a villain of his own creation, fights to save a family he doesn't know, and finally faces the realization that he may notbe prepared for life as a super after all. Plus, the return of Teritan!

This issue leads directly into Volume 2, where the stakes are higher as Jeff tries to reconcile his multiple personalities, only to discover more secrets lurking beneath his fractured psyche! Witness the birth of a new kind of hero!

For four friends, a relaxing cabin vacation takes a turn for the worse when a blizzard rolls in. Add to that the arrival of a stranger warning that it is coming for them. It wants them dead. But what is it? And how far will they go to protect themselves?

This self-contained, 40 page one-shot is written by Shawn Fracture Gabborin, with beautifully rendered, atmospheric art by Rick Lundeen.

What would you do for love? For Darren Toshida, the answer is far from simple: build a time machine.With his best friends Todd and Mikey in tow, Darren decides to go back to a pivotal time in his life, change history, and get the girl that got away.

Armed with twenty years of experience, the trio returns to the summer of 1987 to mentor their younger selves in the fine art of romance.

From indie mavericks Dave Dwonch, (Space-Time Condominium, SRG Presents: Gnome) and Daniel Logan (Exo-1 and the Rock Solid Steelbots), Back in the Day is a heartfelt and hilarious sci-fi romp that redefines the coming of age tale.

volume.name: New Kids On The Block Chillin'

description: START READING with these Point One issues! The House of Ideas proudly presents its second exciting collection of one-shots that bring the history of its greatest heroes into the modern era. Alpha Flight returns! Daken settles the score with Wolverine! The Avengers Academy meets the program washouts! Who will be the new Ghost Rider? War Machine is rebooted as Iron Man 2.0! The X-Men battle a demonic horde! Herc is hunted by a figure from his past! Young Loki learns about his past! Collecting ALPHA FLIGHT (2011) #0.1, DAKEN: DARK WOLVERINE #9.1, AVENGERS ACADEMY #14.1, GHOST RIDER (2011) #0.1, IRON MAN 2.0 #7.1, X-MEN (2010) #15.1, HERC #6.1, JOURNEY INTO MYSTERY (1952) #626.1, X-FACTOR (1986) #224.1, VILLAINS FOR HIRE #0.1, THUNDERBOLTS #163.1, BLACK PANTHER: THE DEADLIEST MAN ALIVE #523.1 and NEW AVENGERS (2010) #16.1.
